graphic name for someone living or working in a wood, from (Old) French <i>bois</i> ‘wood’ (from Late Latin <i>boscum</i> ‘bush, shrub, undergrowth’, of ancient Germanic origin), or a habitational name from (Le) Bois, the name of several places in various parts of France. This surname is also found in Haiti. Compare   Debois   and the most frequent French form   Dubois  . Compare also   Boie  ,   Boies  , and   Boyce  .","English: variant of   Boyce   and   Boyes  ."]},{"name":"Woods","meanings":["English: variant of   Wood   with plural or post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>.","Irish: adopted as a translation of <b>Ó Cuill</b> ‘descendant of <i>Coll</i>’ (see   Quill  ), or in Ulster of <b>Mac Con Coille</b> ‘son of <i>Cú Choille</i>’, a personal name meaning ‘hound of the wood’, which has also been mistranslated   Cox  , as if formed with <i>coileach</i> ‘cock, rooster’."]}]},{"name":"Lena","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Abstracted from various names ending in these syllables, such as <i>Helena</i> and <i>Magdalena</i>. In the United States it was particularly associated with the singer  Lena Horne  (  1917–2010 )."],"variants":[{"name":"Leena","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Lena ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Lena Wood was born in 1384, in England, United Kingdom. She had at least 2 sons with Thomas Crossland. She died in 1410, in her hometown, at the age of 26."},"et":{"1384–1410":"1384–1410","1375–1460":"1375–1460","1406–Male":"1406–Surnud","1410–1430":"1410–1430","1410":"1410","1430":"1430","1375":"1375","1384":"1384","1460":"1460","1406":"1406","Crossland, Yorkshire, England":"South Crosland, Yorkshire, England","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Crossland, Almondbury, West Yorkshire, England":"Almondbury, Yorkshire, England"},"fi":{"1384–1410":"1384–1410","1375–1460":"1375–1460","1406–Male":"1406–Kuollut","1410–1430":"1410–1430","1410":"1410","1430":"1430","1375":"1375"